-- Barcelona Wants Chelsea’s Petr Cech, Star Says: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2013-09-11T07:44:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-11/barcelona-wants-chelsea-s-petr-cech-star-says-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of
soccer stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable Internet
links.  Cech Out  Barcelona wants to sign Chelsea goalkeeper  Petr Cech  to
replace  Victor Valdes , the  Daily Star  reported.  Cech, 31, is tempted to leave Stamford Bridge after nine
years, and the Blues could replace him with Thibaut Courtois,
who is on loan at Atletico Madrid, according to the Star.  Arsenal Striker  Arsenal is close to signing Romanian striker Ciprian
Marica, who is a free agent after leaving Schalke, the  Daily
Mirror  reported.  The Gunners missed out on signing  Luis Suarez  and Gonzalo
Higuain in the offseason, the Mirror added.  Given Loan  Aston Villa could loan Shay Given to a Championship team
that agrees to subsidize his 3 million-pound ($4.7 million)
salary,  the Guardian  reported.  The 37-year-old goalkeeper hasn’t played in a competitive
game for Villa since January after losing his place to Brad
Guzan, the Guardian added.  Boro Pair  Middlesbrough wants to take Norwich pair Luciano Becchio
and Daniel Ayala on loan after failing to sign them before
transfer deadline day, the  Daily Express  reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
